rComments: He was an amazing professor, easily the best I've had at UofT. He knows his stuff about the history of NA cities and makes the course content fascinating. He is kind and approachable outside of class and gives good feedback.

Probably one of the best professors I've had. Assignments build off each other and are fairly graded. He gives good feedback and is always helpful. Lectures are a bit heavy but otherwise, he's concise with the material and he's knowledgeable about the topics being presented.

rComments: One of the most interesting projects I have worked on in university occurred with Professor Lombardo. He gave me a real freedom to pick a subject and topic I was interested in. While a bit of a dry lecturer, his insights and examples in class are often unexpected and intriguing. A great professor!
